==English==
=== Etymology ===
Named after the 1934 [[Cab Calloway]] song "''Jitter Bug''"

=== Noun ===
'''jitterbug'''
# an [[uptempo]] [[jazz]] or [[swing]] [[dance]] which [[embellishes]] on the [[two-step]] pattern and frequently [[incorporates]] [[acrobatic]] style swing [[steps]]
# one who performs such a dance

=== Intransitive Verb ===
'''jitterbug'''
# the act of performing such a dance